&lt;p>They call it &lt;strong>ReasoningBank&lt;/strong>, and at first glance, it sounds like the next predictable step in the AI hype cycle. Another shiny acronym, another &amp;ldquo;scaling breakthrough.&amp;rdquo; But if you actually read the paper, it&amp;rsquo;s not hype. It&amp;rsquo;s something far stranger. Google basically gave their models a therapist.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>